#### Q10. This code printed `{0, 0}`. How can you fix it?

```go
type Point struct {
  x int
  y int
}

func main() {
  data := []byte(`{"x":1, "y": 2}`)
  var p Point
  if err := json.Unmarshal(data, &p); err != nil {
    fmt.Println("error: ", err)
  } else {
    fmt.Println(p)
  }
}
```

- %OPTION% use `json.Decoder`
- %OPTION% Pass a pointer to `data`
- %OPTION% Make `X` and `Y` exported (uppercase)
- %OPTION% Use field tags

